---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="TinyGoat FAQ | Claude Implementation for Revenue Teams" rawTitle={true} description="Answers to the questions revenue leaders ask before working with TinyGoat. Why Claude, why TinyGoat, and what the work actually looks like.">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden pointer-events-none">
      <div class="absolute -top-1/4 -right-1/4 w-[800px] h-[800px] bg-teal/5 rounded-full blur-[150px]"></div>
      <div class="absolute -bottom-1/4 -left-1/4 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-gold/5 rounded-full blur-[120px]"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="fixed inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-[0.03] mix-blend-multiply" style="background-image: url('/noise.png'); background-repeat: repeat;"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10">
      <Nav />

      <!-- Page Header -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-20 md:py-28 max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-navy text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-[1.05] mb-6">
          Common questions.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Everything revenue leaders ask before reaching out. Including the one question that matters most.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-16 md:py-24 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Featured FAQ -->
          <details open class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border-2 border-teal/30 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300 mb-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-0.5 bg-teal/10 text-teal text-xs font-bold rounded">FEATURED</span>
                <h2 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Why TinyGoat?</h2>
              </div>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Most AI consulting comes from people who understand the technology but have never carried a quota, run a sales pod, or sat in a pipeline review. I have. I come from a background in sales and education, which means I understand both why adoption fails and how to actually train people so it sticks. TinyGoat exists specifically for revenue teams because that is where I have lived, and because Claude is too powerful a tool to leave sitting in a chat window. The work is specific, the expertise is specific, and the results are built for the people doing the actual selling, managing, and growing.
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Two-column FAQ grid -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 items-start">
            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Can you help us with ChatGPT or other AI tools for our revenue team?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                My focus is Claude. That is intentional. I believe it is the right tool for revenue teams and I work with it deeply rather than spreading thin across every platform. That said, if your team is currently using another tool and considering a move to Claude, I can help you think through that transition and what it would look like in practice.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Can you help us with Claude for other parts of the organization?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Right now TinyGoat is focused on revenue teams. That is where the expertise is deepest and where I can deliver the most value. If your revenue org is sorted and you want Claude working across other functions, that is a conversation worth having, but I will be honest about where my lane is and where you might be better served by someone else.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">The AI space moves so fast. What if we are outdated by the time the project is done?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                This is a real concern and one I think about too. The way I approach it is by building for the fundamentals of how your team works rather than optimizing for a specific feature that might change next quarter. Claude will keep evolving and so will the work we build together. That is also part of why "Roam" exists. Staying current is not a one-time project. It is ongoing, and having a thought partner who is paying close attention to where this space is heading means your team does not fall behind.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Do you work with teams just getting started with Claude?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Both. Some teams I work with have had Claude for months and are stuck. Others are starting from scratch. The intake process helps figure out where you are so we can start in the right place. You do not need to have anything figured out before reaching out.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Why TinyGoat and not a larger firm?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Larger firms can do a lot of things. Revenue team AI adoption is not usually one of the things they do well. The work requires understanding how sellers actually operate, how managers coach, and why adoption fails even when the tools are good. That specificity is what TinyGoat is built on. If you need AI transformation across your entire organization, a larger firm might be the right call. If you need Claude working for your revenue team in a way that actually sticks, that is the work we do.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
                <h3 class="text-navy font-semibold text-lg">Why the name TinyGoat?</h3>
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                <p class="mb-4">Named after our pup Santiago, who with his big ears looks like a baby goat. He's the unofficial mascot and chief morale officer.</p>
                <img src="/Santiago.jpeg" alt="Santiago the TinyGoat" class="w-32 h-32 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-md" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Closing CTA -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Still have questions?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg mb-8">Ready to move from access to adoption?</p>
          <button
            onclick="Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/gabby-tinygoat/30min'});return false;"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-gold text-navy font-bold text-lg rounded-full hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-gold/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer"
          >
            Book a Free Intro Call
          </button>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-6">
            Prefer email? <a href="mailto:info@tinygoat.ai" class="text-teal hover:underline">info@tinygoat.ai</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <Footer />
  </main>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why TinyGoat?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most AI consulting comes from people who understand the technology but have never carried a quota, run a sales pod, or sat in a pipeline review. I have. I come from a background in sales and education, which means I understand both why adoption fails and how to actually train people so it sticks. TinyGoat exists specifically for revenue teams because that is where I have lived, and because Claude is too powerful a tool to leave sitting in a chat window. The work is specific, the expertise is specific, and the results are built for the people doing the actual selling, managing, and growing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you help us with ChatGPT or other AI tools for our revenue team?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "My focus is Claude. That is intentional. I believe it is the right tool for revenue teams and I work with it deeply rather than spreading thin across every platform. That said, if your team is currently using another tool and considering a move to Claude, I can help you think through that transition and what it would look like in practice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you help us with Claude for other parts of the organization?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Right now TinyGoat is focused on revenue teams. That is where the expertise is deepest and where I can deliver the most value. If your revenue org is sorted and you want Claude working across other functions, that is a conversation worth having, but I will be honest about where my lane is and where you might be better served by someone else."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "The AI space moves so fast. What if we are outdated by the time the project is done?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "This is a real concern and one I think about too. The way I approach it is by building for the fundamentals of how your team works rather than optimizing for a specific feature that might change next quarter. Claude will keep evolving and so will the work we build together. That is also part of why Roam exists. Staying current is not a one-time project. It is ongoing, and having a thought partner who is paying close attention to where this space is heading means your team does not fall behind."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you work with teams just getting started with Claude?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both. Some teams I work with have had Claude for months and are stuck. Others are starting from scratch. The intake process helps figure out where you are so we can start in the right place. You do not need to have anything figured out before reaching out."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why TinyGoat and not a larger firm?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Larger firms can do a lot of things. Revenue team AI adoption is not usually one of the things they do well. The work requires understanding how sellers actually operate, how managers coach, and why adoption fails even when the tools are good. That specificity is what TinyGoat is built on. If you need AI transformation across your entire organization, a larger firm might be the right call. If you need Claude working for your revenue team in a way that actually sticks, that is the work we do."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why the name TinyGoat?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Named after our pup Santiago, who with his big ears looks like a baby goat. He is the unofficial mascot and chief morale officer."
        }
      }
    ]
  })} />
</Layout>
